#. <section class="sutta" id="sn3.18"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.18:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.18:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. Childless"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.18:0.3"
msgid "18. Kalyāṇamittasutta"
msgstr "18. Good Friends"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.197"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn3.18:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Seated to one side, King Pasenadi said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn3.18:1.3"
msgid ""
"“idha mayhaṃ, bhante, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko "
"udapādi:"
msgstr "“Just now, sir, as I was in private retreat this thought came to mind."

msgctxt "sn3.18:1.4"
msgid ""
"‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, so ca kho kalyāṇamittassa kalyāṇasahāyassa "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa, no pāpamittassa no pāpasahāyassa no "
"pāpasampavaṅkassā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha. But it’s for someone with "
"good friends, companions, and associates, not for someone with bad friends, "
"companions, and associates.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:2.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, mahārāja, evametaṃ, mahārāja."
msgstr ""
"“That’s so true, great king! That’s so true!” said the Buddha. And he "
"repeated the king’s statement, adding:"

msgctxt "sn3.18:2.2"
msgid ""
"Svākkhāto, mahārāja, mayā dhammo. So ca kho kalyāṇamittassa kalyāṇasahāyassa "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa, no pāpamittassa no pāpasahāyassa no "
"pāpasampavaṅkassāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:3.1"
msgid ""
"Ekamidāhaṃ, mahārāja, samayaṃ sakkesu viharāmi nagarakaṃ nāma sakyānaṃ "
"nigamo."
msgstr ""
"“Great king, this one time I was staying in the land of the Sakyans where "
"they have a town named Nagaraka."

msgctxt "sn3.18:3.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, mahārāja, ānando bhikkhu yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho, mahārāja, ānando "
"bhikkhu maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the mendicant Ānanda came to me, bowed, sat down to one side, and said:"

msgctxt "sn3.18:3.3"
msgid ""
"‘upaḍḍhamidaṃ, bhante, brahmacariyassa—yadidaṃ kalyāṇamittatā "
"kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, good friends, companions, and associates are half the spiritual life.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.88"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.198"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vuttāhaṃ, mahārāja, ānandaṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, I said to him:"

msgctxt "sn3.18:4.2"
msgid "‘mā hevaṃ, ānanda, mā hevaṃ, ānanda."
msgstr "‘Not so, Ānanda! Not so, Ānanda!"

msgctxt "sn3.18:4.3"
msgid ""
"Sakalameva hidaṃ, ānanda, brahmacariyaṃ—yadidaṃ kalyāṇamittatā "
"kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā."
msgstr ""
"Good friends, companions, and associates are the whole of the spiritual life."

msgctxt "sn3.18:4.4"
msgid ""
"Kalyāṇamittassetaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ kalyāṇasahāyassa "
"kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāvessati ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ "
"maggaṃ bahulīkarissati."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with good friends, companions, and associates can expect to "
"develop and cultivate the noble eightfold path."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:5.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, ānanda, bhikkhu kalyāṇamitto kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko "
"ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti, ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant with good friends develop and cultivate the noble "
"eightfold path?"

msgctxt "sn3.18:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ "
"nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ, sammāsaṅkappaṃ bhāveti … sammāvācaṃ "
"bhāveti … sammākammantaṃ bhāveti … sammāājīvaṃ bhāveti … sammāvāyāmaṃ "
"bhāveti … sammāsatiṃ bhāveti … sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ "
"virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant develops right view, right thought, right speech, "
"right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right "
"immersion, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as "
"letting go."

msgctxt "sn3.18:5.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, ānanda, bhikkhu kalyāṇamitto kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko "
"ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti, ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant with good friends develops and cultivates the noble "
"eightfold path."

msgctxt "sn3.18:5.4"
msgid ""
"Tadamināpetaṃ, ānanda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā sakalamevidaṃ "
"brahmacariyaṃ—yadidaṃ kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatāti."
msgstr ""
"And here’s another way to understand how good friends are the whole of the "
"spiritual life."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.199"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:6.1"
msgid ""
"Mamañhi, ānanda, kalyāṇamittaṃ āgamma jātidhammā sattā jātiyā parimuccanti, "
"jarādhammā sattā jarāya parimuccanti, byādhidhammā sattā byādhito "
"parimuccanti, maraṇadhammā sattā maraṇena parimuccanti, "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsadhammā sattā "
"sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsehi parimuccanti."
msgstr ""
"For, by relying on me as a good friend, sentient beings who are liable to "
"rebirth, old age, and death, to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and "
"distress are freed from all these things."

msgctxt "sn3.18:6.2"
msgid ""
"Iminā kho etaṃ, ānanda, pariyāyena veditabbaṃ yathā sakalamevidaṃ "
"brahmacariyaṃ—yadidaṃ kalyāṇamittatā kalyāṇasahāyatā kalyāṇasampavaṅkatā’ti."
msgstr ""
"This is another way to understand how good friends are the whole of the "
"spiritual life.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:7.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha te, mahārāja, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So, great king, you should train like this:"

msgctxt "sn3.18:7.2"
msgid "‘kalyāṇamitto bhavissāmi kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko’ti."
msgstr "‘I will have good friends, companions, and associates.’"

msgctxt "sn3.18:7.3"
msgid "Evañhi te, mahārāja, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how you should train."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.89"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:8.1"
msgid ""
"Kalyāṇamittassa te, mahārāja, kalyāṇasahāyassa kalyāṇasampavaṅkassa ayaṃ eko "
"dhammo upanissāya vihātabbo—"
msgstr ""
"When you have good friends, companions, and associates, you should live "
"supported by one thing:"

msgctxt "sn3.18:8.2"
msgid "appamādo kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr "diligence in skillful qualities."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:9.1"
msgid ""
"Appamattassa te, mahārāja, viharato appamādaṃ upanissāya, itthāgārassa "
"anuyantassa evaṃ bhavissati:"
msgstr "When you’re diligent, supported by diligence, your ladies of the harem,"

msgctxt "sn3.18:9.2"
msgid "‘rājā kho appamatto viharati, appamādaṃ upanissāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.18:9.3"
msgid "Handa mayampi appamattā viharāma, appamādaṃ upanissāyā’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.200"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:10.1"
msgid ""
"Appamattassa te, mahārāja, viharato appamādaṃ upanissāya, khattiyānampi "
"anuyantānaṃ evaṃ bhavissati:"
msgstr "aristocrat vassals,"

msgctxt "sn3.18:10.2"
msgid "‘rājā kho appamatto viharati appamādaṃ upanissāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.18:10.3"
msgid "Handa mayampi appamattā viharāma, appamādaṃ upanissāyā’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:11.1"
msgid ""
"Appamattassa te, mahārāja, viharato appamādaṃ upanissāya, balakāyassapi evaṃ "
"bhavissati:"
msgstr "troops,"

msgctxt "sn3.18:11.2"
msgid "‘rājā kho appamatto viharati appamādaṃ upanissāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn3.18:11.3"
msgid "Handa mayampi appamattā viharāma, appamādaṃ upanissāyā’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:12.1"
msgid ""
"Appamattassa te, mahārāja, viharato appamādaṃ upanissāya, "
"negamajānapadassapi evaṃ bhavissati:"
msgstr "and people of town and country will think:"

msgctxt "sn3.18:12.2"
msgid "‘rājā kho appamatto viharati, appamādaṃ upanissāya."
msgstr "‘The king lives diligently, supported by diligence."

msgctxt "sn3.18:12.3"
msgid "Handa mayampi appamattā viharāma, appamādaṃ upanissāyā’ti?"
msgstr "We’d better live diligently, supported by diligence!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:13.1"
msgid ""
"Appamattassa te, mahārāja, viharato appamādaṃ upanissāya, attāpi gutto "
"rakkhito bhavissati—"
msgstr ""
"When you’re diligent, supported by diligence, then not only you yourself,"

msgctxt "sn3.18:13.2"
msgid ""
"itthāgārampi guttaṃ rakkhitaṃ bhavissati, kosakoṭṭhāgārampi guttaṃ rakkhitaṃ "
"bhavissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"but your ladies of the harem, and your treasury and storehouses will be "
"guarded and protected.”"

msgctxt "sn3.18:13.3"
msgid "Idamavoca … pe …"
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. …"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.201"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:14.1"
msgid "“Bhoge patthayamānena,"
msgstr "“For one who desires a continuous flow"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.18:14.2"
msgid "uḷāre aparāpare;"
msgstr "of exceptional wealth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.18:14.3"
msgid "Appamādaṃ pasaṃsanti,"
msgstr "the astute praise diligence"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.18:14.4"
msgid "puññakiriyāsu paṇḍitā;"
msgstr "in making merit."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.18:14.5"
msgid "Appamatto ubho atthe,"
msgstr "Being diligent, an astute person"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.18:14.6"
msgid "adhiggaṇhāti paṇḍito."
msgstr "secures both benefits:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.18:15.1"
msgid "Diṭṭhe dhamme ca yo attho,"
msgstr "the benefit in this life,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.18:15.2"
msgid "yo cattho samparāyiko;"
msgstr "and in lives to come."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.18:15.3"
msgid "Atthābhisamayā dhīro,"
msgstr "A sage, comprehending the meaning,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.18:15.4"
msgid "paṇḍitoti pavuccatī”ti."
msgstr "is called ‘astute’.”"
